org.neo4j.graphmatching
Interface ValueMatcher

Deprecated. 

@Deprecated
public interface ValueMatcher

An interface which abstracts value matching. Examples of value matchers would be: exact matchi, regex match a.s.o. Also look at CommonValueMatchers.

Method Summary
 boolean matches(Object value)
          Deprecated. Tries to match value to see if it matches an expected value.
 

Method Detail

matches

boolean matches(Object value)
Deprecated. 
Tries to match value to see if it matches an expected value. value is null if the property wasn't found on the Node or Relationship it came from. The value can be of type array, where ArrayPropertyUtil can be of help.

Parameters:
value - the value from a Node or Relationship to match against an expected value.
Returns:
true if the value matches, else false.
